All is set for the 52nd National Board Meeting of the Bible Society of Nigeria (BSN) slated for tomorrow July 22 – 26, in Yola, Adamawa State.  BSN’s Manager (Media and Public Relations), Bejamin Mordi, explained that Board Meeting will be declared open by the Adamawa State Governor, Rt Hon. Ahmadu Fintiri.  The Patron of BSN and former Head of State, Dr. Yakubu Gowon, is expected to grace the event alongside trustees, national officers, delegates from across the country and some senior members of the management team of the organization.  The meeting, which is being hosted by the North-east Zone of the BSN, will be presided over by the President of the Society, Dr. Aaron Nuhu.  “Among other things, the Board Meeting will discuss past and future activities of the organization concerning Bible work and examine her accounts for the past one year.  “The General Secretary/CEO of the BSN, Dr. Dare Ajiboye is expected to present his report for the year under review to the Board at the meeting.  “It will start with a Divine Service scheduled to hold on Wednesday, July 24th,” Mordi said.